A reminder that our next Identity WG meeting will be next Wednesday, July 27, at 12pm EDT / 9am PDT. If you are attending the Hyperledger Hackathon in San Francisco, we will be using the boardroom upstairs at 9am  for the call. 

The topic of this meeting is our 3rd discussion with David Kravitz over the course of July on the IBM’s Membership Services architecture as used by Hyperledger Fabric. Please ask questions in advance of our next meeting in Slack's <#C114SSX41> channel or post in our Google Doc (see below).

The recording of the 1st Identity WG meeting on IBM’s Membership Services architecture as used by Hyperledger Fabric is available at: <https://meetings.webex.com/collabs/url/i-271A2F8IRqjuDCoiWed_-ISAS5bOQTOm-1Vi5O_GS00000>

The slides for this 1st meeting are at: <https://www.dropbox.com/s/d4geya90fbv3kw2/Hyperledger%20Membership%20Services%20Presentation%20June%2029%202016.pdf?dl=0>

The recording for the 2nd meeting is available at: <https://meetings.webex.com/collabs/url/Sc3lILQRtXr7MwxQW7UITCPN7EDMsVrJT9Ie4r3VjiG00000>

The slides for the 2nd meeting are available at: <https://www.dropbox.com/s/4my9v4uo9ynn8kf/2016-07-13_MembershipServicesInHyperledgerFabric_Part2.pdf?dl=0>
